; SumatraLister.def
; Exports the WLX (Lister plugin) API with plain, undecorated names so that
; Total Commander (which loads these by name via GetProcAddress) can find
; them regardless of calling-convention name-mangling.
;
; Deliberately no LIBRARY statement here: this .def file is shared by both
; the 32-bit build (output SumatraLister.wlx) and the 64-bit build (output
; SumatraLister.wlx64). A hardcoded LIBRARY name always mismatches one of
; the two, which MSVC reports as LNK4070 ("/OUT:... directive in .EXP
; differs from output filename ...; ignoring directive") at final link
; time. The warning is harmless either way -- it only matters for programs
; that implicitly/statically link against the generated .lib, and Total
; Commander instead loads this plugin via LoadLibrary + GetProcAddress by
; name, which never touches that metadata -- but omitting LIBRARY avoids it
; entirely for both architectures: without it, the linker derives the
; expected name from the real /OUT: target rather than from a static string
; here, so there's nothing left to mismatch.

EXPORTS
    ListGetDetectString
    ListLoad
    ListLoadW
    ListLoadNext
    ListLoadNextW
    ListCloseWindow
    ListSendCommand
    ListSearchText
    ListSearchTextW
    ListSearchDialog
    ListGetPreviewBitmap
    ListGetPreviewBitmapW
    ListPrint
    ListPrintW
    ListSetDefaultParams
